9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 536, L.D. 1306, “An Act to Continue the
10 Exemption for Polystyrene Foam Disposable Food Service Containers Prepackaged at
11 Wholesale”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
13 emergency clause and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §1571, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2021, c. 208, §1, is further
15 amended by amending the first blocked paragraph to read:
16 This subsection is repealed July 1, 2025 2027.
17 Sec. 2. 38 MRSA §1571, sub-§3-A, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 208, §2, is amended
18 by amending the first blocked paragraph to read:
19 This subsection is effective July 1, 2025 2027.
20 Sec. 3. 38 MRSA §1572, sub-§3, ¶C, as amended by PL 2021, c. 208, §4, is further
21 amended by amending the first blocked paragraph to read:
22 This paragraph is repealed July 1, 2025 2027.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment replaces the bill and amends the law governing disposable food
2277 service containers as follows.
28 1. It provides that the provision of that law that is currently set to take effect July 1,
29 2025, which will define "disposable food service container" to include service ware used
30 to contain, transport or otherwise package raw, uncooked or butchered meat, poultry, fish,
31 seafood or eggs, will instead take effect July 1, 2027.
32 2. It provides that the provision of that law that is currently set to be repealed July 1,
33 2025 and defines "disposable food service container" to not include service ware used to
